                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.899,
                                "byte_start": 89002,
                                "byte_stop": 128604,
                                "text": "Justice Breyer has the opinion in 05-259, Burlington Northern and Santa Fe Railway versus White."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.899,
                        "stop": 353.332,
                        "byte_start": 128604,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15139,
                            "name": "Stephen G. Breyer",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/stephen_g_breyer",
                            "last_name": "Breyer",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2785,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 775890000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2785"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32682,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49908,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/stephen_g_breyer_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 7777,
                            "identifier": "stephen_g_breyer"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.899,
                                "stop": 31.875,
                                "byte_start": 128604,
                                "byte_stop": 216584,
                                "text": "Section 703 of the \u2026 of Title VII of the Civil Rights Act -- that\u2019s the employment section -- forbids an employer from discriminating against an individual because of race, religion, gender or national origin with respect to \u201ccompensation, terms, conditions or privileges of employment\u201d."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 31.875,
                                "stop": 50.036,
                                "byte_start": 216584,
                                "byte_stop": 289204,
                                "text": "Then you go to the next section, which is 704, and the next section forbids an employer from discriminating against an individual because that individual has filed a charge or assisted in an investigation of or imposed -- opposed an employer\u2019s discriminatory behavior."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.036,
                                "stop": 56.324,
                                "byte_start": 289204,
                                "byte_stop": 314386,
                                "text": "In other words it forbids retaliation when you complain about a Title VII violation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.324,
                                "stop": 100.105,
                                "byte_start": 314386,
                                "byte_stop": 489511,
                                "text": "Now, in this case, we consider 704, the anti-retaliation provision, and what we do is, we are focusing on two matters that the lower courts have reached different conclusions about:  the first, we ask, \u201cWell, does that anti-retaliation provision limit the kind of retaliation it forbids; two, retaliation that affects terms and conditions of an individual\u2019s employment; or does it contain no such limitation, does it go further?\u201d; second, we ask, \u201dHow harmful must the forbidden retaliation be in order to fall within the scope of the provision which prohibits it?\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 100.105,
                                "stop": 110.75,
                                "byte_start": 489511,
                                "byte_stop": 532039,
                                "text": "Now, as to the first question, we find that the provision is not limited to retaliation; it affects the terms and conditions of an individual\u2019s employment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 110.75,
                                "stop": 112.258,
                                "byte_start": 532039,
                                "byte_stop": 538099,
                                "text": "It goes farther."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.258,
                                "stop": 126.261,
                                "byte_start": 538099,
                                "byte_stop": 594106,
                                "text": "It forbids retaliation that affects an individual outside of his job, say, serious harassment in his home, just is it forbids retaliation on the job, say, a demotion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 126.261,
                                "stop": 128.534,
                                "byte_start": 594106,
                                "byte_stop": 603196,
                                "text": "The language of the statute suggests this."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.534,
                                "stop": 138.007,
                                "byte_start": 603196,
                                "byte_stop": 641126,
                                "text": "That\u2019s why I read the text, because the text that I read that talks about limitations to employment is in the first part, the substantive provision, 703."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 138.007,
                                "stop": 143.538,
                                "byte_start": 641126,
                                "byte_stop": 663173,
                                "text": "No language like that is present in the second part, so why limit it?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.538,
                                "stop": 147.182,
                                "byte_start": 663173,
                                "byte_stop": 677802,
                                "text": "And moreover, common sense suggests the same thing."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 147.182,
                                "stop": 167.197,
                                "byte_start": 677802,
                                "byte_stop": 757841,
                                "text": "After all, a threat to hurt a person who files a complaint at that individual\u2019s home or to file a false criminal charge against a victim of discrimination could be just as effective at stopping her from filling the complaint as a threat to reduce her pay."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 167.197,
                                "stop": 182.113,
                                "byte_start": 757841,
                                "byte_stop": 817505,
                                "text": "So limiting the anti-retaliation to employment-related acts would fail to fully achieve the provision\u2019s purpose, which is to prevent employers from interfering with employees\u2019 efforts to invoke Title VII\u2019s protections."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 182.113,
                                "stop": 197.348,
                                "byte_start": 817505,
                                "byte_stop": 878422,
                                "text": "As to the second question, we hold that the anti-retaliation provision protects an individual not from all conceivable retaliation, but from retaliation that produces a significant injury or harm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 197.348,
                                "stop": 201.646,
                                "byte_start": 878422,
                                "byte_stop": 895663,
                                "text": "Of course, you want to know what\u0027s meant by \u201csignificant\u201d."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 201.646,
                                "stop": 209.832,
                                "byte_start": 895663,
                                "byte_stop": 928369,
                                "text": "Well, we say what it means is, we adopt the standard that\u2019s been used by the 7th Circuit and the District of Columbia Circuits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 209.832,
                                "stop": 232.467,
                                "byte_start": 928369,
                                "byte_stop": 1018961,
                                "text": "They say and we say, to show that an injury or harm is significant, the plaintiff must show that a reasonable employee would have found the employer\u2019s retaliatory action materially adverse, which in this context means that it well might have dissuaded a reasonable worker from making or supporting a charge of discrimination."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 232.467,
                                "stop": 238.407,
                                "byte_start": 1018961,
                                "byte_stop": 1042680,
                                "text": "We use the term \u201cmaterial\u201d to separate out, because they are not actionable, trivial harms."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 238.407,
                                "stop": 247.886,
                                "byte_start": 1042680,
                                "byte_stop": 1080610,
                                "text": "We refer to the reactions of a reasonable person, because we think the standard for judging harm must be objective, as it is in other Title VII context."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 247.886,
                                "stop": 260.135,
                                "byte_start": 1080610,
                                "byte_stop": 1129616,
                                "text": "We phrase the standard in general terms, because the significance of any given retaliatory act will often depend upon particular circumstances; that is to say, context matters."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 260.135,
                                "stop": 270.816,
                                "byte_start": 1129616,
                                "byte_stop": 1172352,
                                "text": "A worker\u2019s schedule change may normally make little difference to a worker; but suppose that that worker is a young mother with children, then it could matter enormously."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 270.816,
                                "stop": 288.122,
                                "byte_start": 1172352,
                                "byte_stop": 1241524,
                                "text": "A supervisor\u2019s refusal to invite an employee to lunch is normally just a petty slight; but to retaliate by excluding an employee from a weekly training lunch might well dissuade a reasonable employee from coming forward with a discrimination complaint."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 288.122,
                                "stop": 291.924,
                                "byte_start": 1241524,
                                "byte_stop": 1256780,
                                "text": "Finally, we apply the standard to the facts of this case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 291.924,
                                "stop": 301.799,
                                "byte_start": 1256780,
                                "byte_stop": 1296277,
                                "text": "The plaintiff, the only woman working as a railroad-track laborer in the railroad\u0027s Tennessee yard complained about sexual harassment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 301.799,
                                "stop": 305.184,
                                "byte_start": 1296277,
                                "byte_stop": 1309756,
                                "text": "Subsequently, she was subject to a change of duties."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 305.184,
                                "stop": 309.993,
                                "byte_start": 1309756,
                                "byte_stop": 1328982,
                                "text": "Her duty was changed from forklift operator to ordinary track worker."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 309.993,
                                "stop": 319.118,
                                "byte_start": 1328982,
                                "byte_stop": 1365554,
                                "text": "Then she made some more complaints, and after that she was charged with insubordination and suspended without pay for 37 days."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 319.118,
                                "stop": 324.689,
                                "byte_start": 1365554,
                                "byte_stop": 1387810,
                                "text": "Eventually, the railroad found her innocent of insubordination and gave her back pay."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 324.689,
                                "stop": 340.387,
                                "byte_start": 1387810,
                                "byte_stop": 1450609,
                                "text": "In our view, the jury could lawfully find in the circumstance that the reassignment of her job duties, and the 37-day suspension without pay, even though she later got back pay, they still could find that that constituted unlawful retaliation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 340.387,
                                "stop": 343.702,
                                "byte_start": 1450609,
                                "byte_stop": 1463879,
                                "text": "We explain all these matters more fully in our opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 343.702,
                                "stop": 348.526,
                                "byte_start": 1463879,
                                "byte_stop": 1483209,
                                "text": "The judgment of the United States Court of Appeals, which found in her favor, is affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 348.526,
                                "stop": 353.332,
                                "byte_start": 1483209,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has filed a separate opinion concurring in the judgment."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
